WEBVTT

00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:08.320
During normal operation, check the governor for any abnormal noise.

00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:17.920
Make sure that the elevator cannot move and perform a visual check on all parts of the governor.

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:21.360
Check that the seals are present and not broken.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:26.720
Engage the governor with a screwdriver and open the cover.

00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:40.600
Measure the height of the brake lining in engaged position It must be 21mm or more Check the movability of the movable parts.

00:00:41.040 --> 00:00:43.760
Report if any part is not free to move.

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:55.440
Check wire rope strands for broken wire and rust bleeding If necessary, replace the governor rope.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.560
Reset the governor as shown in the video.

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:08.880
Activate the safety switch and check the correct function.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.840
Clean dust and dirt off the overspeed governor.

00:01:17.360 --> 00:01:20.400
close the overspeed governor cover and lock it.

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:31.920
Check the governor cover does not touch the pulley If there is any noise from the cover during operation, adjust the cover until not touching.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.520
If applicable, check the Tacho Belt tension It must not be too tight or too loose.

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:45.280
The Tacho Belt tension gauge should just firmly fit in.

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:53.360
Check the Tacho Belt cable is in good condition and not damaged.

